__d(function(g,r,i,a,m,e,d){"use strict";Object.defineProperty(e,'__esModule',{value:!0}),Object.defineProperty(e,"CHAPTERS",{enumerable:!0,get:function(){return t}});const t=[{id:1,name:'The Thicket',arrivalBeat:"You wake under a tangle of branches, no name and no past. Berries hang within reach; a hare watches from the brush. Find the thicket's edge before the dark does.",introText:"You wake under a tangle of branches, no name and no past \u2014 only the cold, and time pressing down. Berries hang within reach, twigs litter the floor, a hare watches from the brush. Find the edge of the thicket before the dark finds you.",firstActionIds:['gather_redberry'],gateActionId:'clear_thicket_edge',essenceReward:10},{id:2,name:'The Hollow',arrivalBeat:"Past the thicket the ground folds into a damp hollow. Logs worth splitting, a river cold and full, clay begging to be fired. Build well, eat better than berries, and descend when the walls no longer hold you.",introText:"Past the thicket the ground folds into a damp hollow ringed by older, thicker trees. Logs here are worth splitting, the river runs cold and full, and clay in the banks begs to be fired. Build well, eat better than berries, and descend when the walls of the hollow no longer hold you back.",firstActionIds:['cut_log','gather_fiber'],gateActionId:'descend_hollow',essenceReward:14},{id:3,name:'Ridge & Cleft',arrivalBeat:"The land splits as surely as your choices will. The cleft drops into shadow and wrings vigor from danger; the ridge climbs toward storage that outlives you. Choose your path, then cross.",introText:"The land splits as surely as your choices will. To one side a narrow cleft drops into shadow, where vigor is wrung from danger; to the other a long ridge climbs toward open storage and steadier footing. Take the cleft for the strength it leaves in your bones, or the ridge to carry more of everything \u2014 then cross.",firstActionIds:['dig_clay','gather_windfall','tame_ridge_goat','spar_ridge_bear','take_cleft','take_ridge'],gateActionId:'cross_ridge',essenceReward:18},{id:4,name:'Geode Hollows',arrivalBeat:"Hollow stones, each cupping a gem. What you pry loose decides what you become: axe, pick, bow, spade, or clasp. Choose your tools, forge them, and break for the open air.",introText:"Hollows of hollow stone, each cupping a dull, bright, or deep-lit gem. What you pry loose decides what you can become: an axe for the timber, a pick for the rock, a bow for the hunt, a spade for the earth, a clasp to carry your own weight. Choose your tools and forge them, then break for the open air.",firstActionIds:['open_dim_geode','open_bright_geode','open_deep_geode','fish_eel','bake_pie'],gateActionId:'leave_hollows',essenceReward:25},{id:5,name:'The Highlands',arrivalBeat:"The world opens onto wind-scoured highlands. Boar root the slopes; lodges rise against the cold; and coiled in the pass, the Wyrm waits. Build high, hunt hard \u2014 and don't face it until your heart can take it.",introText:"The air thins and the world opens onto wind-scoured highlands. Boar root the slopes, lodges and longhouses can be raised against the cold, and far above, coiled in the pass, the Wyrm waits. This is where a body is truly forged \u2014 build high, hunt hard, and do not face the Wyrm until your heart can take it.",firstActionIds:['hunt_boar','forage_highland','spar_dummy','face_wyrm'],gateActionId:'summit_pass',essenceReward:33},{id:6,name:'The Tide Reach',arrivalBeat:"The highlands fall away to tide and reef. A raft will carry you to crab, coconut, and the great reef lobster \u2014 and to the jaguar that guards them. Take the sea's richest food, then breach the reach.",introText:"The highlands fall away to a churning reach of tide and reef. A raft will carry you north, west, and east to crab, coconut, and the great reef lobster \u2014 and to a jaguar that prowls the breakers. Gather the sea's richest food, conquer what guards it, and breach the reach. Beyond it lies the end of this world, and the beginning of the next.",firstActionIds:['catch_crab','gather_coconut','gather_driftwood'],gateActionId:'breach_the_reach',essenceReward:45},{id:7,name:'The Fellwater',arrivalBeat:"The river carries you into a drowned forest \u2014 trunks like towers, water loud between them. Something pale keeps count of your kills. Here the axe is the whole of the law: fell, haul, cart. Then break the logjam.",introText:"The reach narrows to a broad brown river, and the river carries you into a drowned forest \u2014 trunks like towers, water loud between them. Pelicans ride the shallows, a great bull grazes the cut-lines, and something pale keeps count of your kills from the dark timber. Here the axe is the whole of the law: fell, haul, cart, and let nothing you cannot eat sit idle. When the felled wood chokes the river into a groaning jam, break it \u2014 and ride the flood out of this world\u2019s green heart.",firstActionIds:['fell_riverwood','snare_pelican','scout_upriver'],gateActionId:'break_the_logjam',essenceReward:61},{id:8,name:'The Mudbank',arrivalBeat:"The flood spends you onto a grey shore where the river forgets its name. Limestone ribs the bank; seals haul out fat and unbothered. Dig, cut stone, cook what you catch, then teach the old walrus who keeps this shore.",introText:"The flood does not so much carry you as spend you, and what is left washes up on a grey shore where the river forgets its name in a cold, slack sea. The mud takes every footprint and gives nothing back; limestone shows its pale ribs through the bank, and a rusted rail runs from a half-cut quarry down to water the color of iron. Seals haul out fat and unbothered on the flats, and the poachers who laid that rail will show you the hauling-grounds \u2014 for company, and for a share of what you bleed catching. Dig, because the mud yields nothing freely. Cut stone, because this shore respects nothing else, and cook what you catch while it still steams. The old walrus has drowned better than you in that deep water. Take the pick in both hands and teach it that the shore has a new keeper.",firstActionIds:['dig_the_mudflats','scout_the_mudbank'],gateActionId:'face_the_walrus',essenceReward:82},{id:9,name:'The Cinderway',arrivalBeat:"Past the mudbank the coast catches fire. The cliffs are glass, seamed with rock that never learned to be cold. No beast holds this shore; the shore itself is the argument. Chip. Lash. Run. When the flow moves, outrun it.",introText:"Past the mudbank the coast stands up and catches fire. The cliffs here are glass \u2014 the mountain\u2019s old tempers, cooled mid-shout \u2014 and down their faces run slow orange seams of rock that never learned to be cold. No beast holds this shore; the shore itself is the argument. Fish still rise fat in the scalded pools, obsidian chips clean under the pick, and a quarry porter with forearms like mooring rope will lend you his sledge if you can put his hand to the stone. High above, one bare path threads the lava fields, older than any map, crossed by no one you will ever meet \u2014 and past it, the caldera rim waits. Chip the glass. Lash a rod. Run the scree until your feet stop asking permission. The mountain does not fight you. It only counts your steps, and it counts fast. When the flow moves, do not fight that either. Outrun it.",firstActionIds:['chip_obsidian','scout_the_cinderway'],gateActionId:'outrun_the_flow',essenceReward:110},{id:10,name:'The Vault',arrivalBeat:"Stairs of dressed stone drop out of the daylight; the first built thing you have found. Traders keep lamps on the middle floor. Below everything, the door: no lock, no keeper. It is a ledger; it opens for a sum.",introText:"Past the caldera the world stops being made by weather and starts being made by hands. Stairs of dressed stone drop out of the daylight into a hall too straight to be any cave \u2014 the first built thing you have found since you first woke, and it is not empty. Lamps burn on the middle floor, kept by traders who have outwaited the mountain itself; they will weigh your smoked seal and your scalded perch against pale koi and never once ask your name. Below the lamps the dark grows its own harvest, gloomcaps fat on drowned timbers, and below the gloomcaps lies still black water, and below everything else, the door. It has no lock and no keeper and no hunger you can fight. It is a ledger. It counts what came down the stairs \u2014 every life, every meal, every hauled and hoarded thing \u2014 and it opens for a sum, not a struggle. Glean the old bronze. Feed the dark, and let it feed you back. Trade like the mountain is listening. And when your accounts weigh more than your fear, go down and breach the door. The last world is waiting behind it, and it is already awake.",firstActionIds:['glean_old_bronze','enter_the_antehall'],gateActionId:'breach_the_vault_door',essenceReward:149},{id:11,name:'The First',arrivalBeat:"The door opens on sky \u2014 and the First, sitting the way mountains sit. It woke with no name, the same as you, and could not finish dying. Wake it. Take it apart. End its first life, and keep yours.",introText:"The door does not open on a room. It opens on sky \u2014 a bowl of country the old builders roofed with weather, and in the middle of it, sitting the way mountains sit, the First. It was here before the thicket, before the traders, before the ash and the mud and the drowned timbers. It woke with no name and no past, the same as you, and it could not finish dying \u2014 so the world has been spending lives against its account ever since, yours among them. Every time you drowned, it felt it. Every time you woke, so did it. You are its echo, and it knows you the way a wound knows weather. Clams school in its flooded footprints, honey drips from the hives stacked along its shoulders, pale mushrooms fatten in its shade \u2014 the world will feed you the whole time you kill it, because that is what the world has always done. Wake it. Take it apart a joint at a time, and die as often as it takes; you have practiced dying longer than anything alive. The cold arithmetic that pressed down on your first morning was never the dark\u2019s. It was this ledger, and today it closes. End the First\u2019s life, and the next one you wake into is yours to keep. You woke with no name. Go and take one.",firstActionIds:['scout_the_titanfield','spar_the_titans_shadow'],gateActionId:'end_the_first_life',essenceReward:201}]},201,[]);
